PROCESS:
1. For TS4114 (override modifier missing): the base class declares the same member as the subclass — add `override` keyword.
2. For TS18048 (possibly undefined): use optional chaining `?.` or a nullish check around the access.
3. For TS7006 (implicit any): add JSDoc `@param` annotation matching the function signature.
4. For TS2540 (assign to read-only): the field was likely declared as readonly via JSDoc or class field syntax. Either:
   (a) Remove the readonly modifier in the type declaration (preferred if the H01 fix legitimately needs to mutate it).
   (b) Use a mutator approach that doesn't reassign — e.g., assign to `/** @type {any} */(this)._customPrecompiles`.
   Look at the H01 commit to see the intent; if the fix swaps to a per-instance array (the H01 finding was "Custom precompile state is shared and mutated across EVM instances"), the field needs to be mutable on the instance. Make sure the type declaration reflects that.

